# [[resolute]]; [[decisive]]; [[firm]]
#: {{zh-x|曾子 曰：「士 不 可以 不 弘 毅，任 重 而 道 遠。仁 以 為 己 任，不 亦 重 乎？死 而 後 已，不 亦 遠 乎？」|The philosopher Zeng said, "The officer may not be without breadth of mind and '''vigorous endurance'''. His burden is heavy and his course is long. Perfect virtue is the burden which he considers it is his to sustain - is it not heavy? Only with death does his course stop - is it not long?"|ref=Analects|collapsed=y|CL}}
